-- Nortel sees higher first-quarter revenue
-- 
-- Tue May 1, 2007 8:48pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/05/02/us-nortel-outlook-idUSWEN746620070502

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Nortel Networks Corp. NT.TO on Tuesday forecast a 4 percent rise in 2007 first-quarter revenue and confirmed its full-year revenue forecast. 

 The company forecast first-quarter revenue of about $2.48 billion, above the consensus analysts' estimate of $2.4 billion, according to Reuters Estimates. It forecast full-year revenue to be flat to down slightly compared with 2006. Analysts are expecting revenue of about $11.33 billion, on average, according to Reuters Estimates. Nortel also said it has appointed David Drinkwater as chief financial officer on an interim basis, effective May 1.